package.json
> Entry Point To the application
> First file that starts with
> MetaData (name, version, description)
> Scripts(start,test,build)

////////////////
**Step To Generate Package.json
////////////////////////////////
*NodeJs must be installed in the system
> go inside the folder using cmd/terminal
> type npm init
> answer all question
> type "yes"

////////////////////////////////
npm init -y

////////////////
**Step To install package
////////////////////////////////
*NodeJs must be installed in the system
> go inside the folder using cmd/terminal
> type npm i packagename /npm install packagename / npm install packagename --save /
    type npm i packagename@version
>

npm start
npm run filename

child process

> 4 core


local dependency  > npm i packagename
dev dependency    > npm i packagename --save-dev

global dependency  (start, build, compile, generate)

# window
> open cmd as administrator
> npm i -g packagename

#mac /linux
> open terminal
> sudo npm i -g packagename


# Cd(continous development)
> npm i -g nodemon